  "texts": [
    "Sentiment Analysis LLMs struggle with continuous-valued regression and formatting precision (rounding/decimal mismatch).",
    "FiQA Task 1: model outputs \"0.512\" vs. ground truth \"0.51,\" leading to higher MSE than expected.",
    "Identifying cause-effect requires deep reasoning beyond surface patterns, which zero-shot models lack.",
    "CD: models miss linking an interest-rate hike to an observed bond-price drop.",
    "Abstractive gaps and potential data contamination can inflate extractive metrics."
